section.para:
      		The following is a part of ProductServiceImpl.java code to record a
				log message
				using basic how-to-use.				
      					/**
 * According to the file definition of src/main/resources/log4j.xml,
 logger name searches for logger relevant to anyframe.example.logging package
 and records a log message through the logger in this test.
 */
@Service("productService")
public class ProductServiceImpl extends GenericServiceImpl<Product, String>
        implements ProductService {

    public Page getPagingList(ProductSearchVO searchVO) throws Exception {
        ProductService.LOGGER.debug("DEBUG - call getPagingList.");
        ProductService.LOGGER.info("INFO - call getPagingList.");
        ProductService.LOGGER.warn("WARN - call getPagingList.");
        ProductService.LOGGER.error("ERROR - call getPagingList.");
        ProductService.LOGGER.fatal("FATAL ERROR - call getPagingList.");
        return null;
    }
}

			The following is a part of LoggingSampleServiceImpl.java recording a log
				message using messageSource bean.			
      		public class LoggingSampleServiceImpl implements LoggingSampleService,
        ApplicationContextAware {
    private MessageSource messageSource = null;
    public void setApplicationContext(ApplicationContext applicationContext)
        throws BeansException {
        this.messageSource = (MessageSource) applicationContext.getBean("messageSource");
    }
    // ...
}

      		The following is LoggingSampleService.java, an interface class
				which defined logger to use in service implementation class.				
      		public interface LoggingSampleService {
    String ROLE = LoggingSampleService.class.getName();
    // Define logger to use at LoggingSampleServiceImpl.
    Log LOGGER = LogFactory.getLog(LoggingSampleService.class);
    public String greet();
}

			The following is a part of LoggingSampleServiceImpl.java, implementation class
			which records log message by using ResourceBundle.		
      		public String greet() {
    // Records a log message using ResourceBundle. (When there is no argument)
    LoggingSampleService.LOGGER.debug(messageSource.getMessage(
        "sample.default.msg", new String[] {}, Locale.getDefault()));
    // Records a log message using ResourceBundle. (When there is one argument)
    LoggingSampleService.LOGGER.debug(messageSource.getMessage(
        "sample.msg", new String[] { "GilDong" }, Locale.getDefault()));
    return "Hello";
}
